Obviously not. The monster just roared and tried to charge directly at Sasalin. Thank goodness, although Sasalin was large in size, he was still quite agile and managed to dodge in time. However, Nisi couldn't help but scream, and almost slipped off Sasalin's smooth scales.
"How can we kill them?" Nisi shouted.
"Aim for their heads!"
"This is too hard!"
Sasalin roared, circled around, and flew toward the mountain he called home. The black monster followed closely, but when attacked from behind by fire, it became somewhat panicked. The monster had not yet realized it had gained another opponent. Sasalin slowed down, then struck the monster's head with his tail, knocking it off course, which made the monster even more panicked.
The monster roared, emitting a hissing sound from its throat, flying straight upward while continuously spitting something into the air. Suddenly, everything around became pitch black, as if the monster was absorbing the light from the sky and replacing it with an eternal night.
Sasalin's vision went black, and he tried to retreat, but found himself colliding with tree branches and then falling to the ground. The monster seemed to clearly know where Sasalin had fallen, flying directly toward him and bringing the cloud of darkness with it.
"Kayer!" Tenuk shouted, flying out of the cloud and beginning to circle, trying to locate Nisi and Sasalin in the darkness below. "What should we do, Kayer...? Kayer, where are you?"
Nisi struggled to stand up. She felt certain she had broken bones, but her strange, unnatural healing ability had already begun to take effect. Sasalin's situation was different; he lay helplessly on the ground, leaning against a tree he had knocked down. Nisi tried to walk toward Sasalin, but she could barely see anything due to the darkness. Terrifying shadows filled the area, and something was screaming within them.
A terrible club-like tail suddenly smashed into the ground, throwing Nisi to the ground. She noticed the tail was swinging wildly, but its target did not seem to be her. Nisi barely saw the monster roaring and furiously scratching at the shadows it had created. Something was teleporting through the darkness, waiting for an opportunity to strike the monster.
Suddenly, a gunshot pierced the air, and the monster immediately fell silent, collapsing motionless to the ground. The surrounding darkness dissipated, revealing the truth of the situation. Kayel stood on the monster's corpse, holding a rifle, breathing heavily.
"That was... one of the strangest shadow jumps I've ever done... Tanto Kartolon..." Kayel gasped. For some reason, his eyes glowed with black light, and a dark energy surged within him. But just as Kayel spoke, his organic armor regained its color, and his eyes returned to their normal yellow.
After a while, Nisi finally understood what had happened. They all knew that Kayel possessed strange shadow abilities, but he rarely used them, as most people considered such abilities extremely evil and terrifying. However, Nisi did not know that Kayel could use this ability in any darkness. Moreover, from Kayel's expression, it was clear that he himself was also very surprised.
"Are you okay?" Nisi couldn't help but ask.
"I'm fine. I killed that thing, and I'll be okay soon." Kayel looked at his "work," and at that moment, Tenuk landed beside him, transforming back into his original Spast form.
Now, the monster was motionless, and they could finally take a good look at what it actually was. Its skin was jet black and shiny, covered with a slimy liquid that clung tightly to its body. It had four wings and four legs, each ending in long claws, and two straight horns grew from its skull.
Before Tenuk and Kayer could even ask what in the world this thing was, another monster screamed and leaped out from the nearby bushes. At that moment, a familiar car crashed into the side of the monster, sending it sliding a short distance before coming to a stop at Nisi's feet. Without hesitation, Nisi grabbed his shotgun and fired directly at the monster's head, killing it instantly.
"Ugh..." Retwick muttered from the driver's seat, then clumsily turned off the engine and climbed out of the truck. "Uh, I didn't mean to... Are you all okay?"
"You missed all the fun!" Tenuk said, annoyed. "Where were you?"
"You left me behind. I did my best to get here..." Retwick sighed. "Excuse me, what were those horrible things?"
Retvik's question was answered by Sasalin, who had already risen to his feet. He was covered in wounds and scratches, looking a bit dazed, but his injuries did not seem serious.
"You killed the Corrupted! Those infected monsters. When the Corruption attacked your god, these beings were left here."
"You mean... we... helped kill the terrible monster god?" Tenuk stammered.
"Yes, that's right. There may be more Corrupted. But I can't shoot them in the head. I don't have a gun. And it's not fair, one on two, right?" Sasalin walked up to Kayer, patted his head. "Thank you, little guy. You remind me of my old friend Arcadine. Just you aren't as ruthless, nor do you have as powerful a destructive ability as him."
"Uh... thank you... I guess..." Kayer shrugged. "So, uh, did we complete the mission?"
Nisi shrugged, picked up her camera, and took several pictures of the monsters that were definitely dead. Then, she drew out her favorite knife—the exquisite Death's Knife—and began cutting off one of the monster's horns, then the other. However, the moment Nisi finished cutting, the monsters suddenly began to combust, quickly turning into a pile of ashes. The horns Nisi had cut off also turned to ash.
"Well... that's certainly a mixed blessing..." Nisi sighed. "At least I still have the photos, right?"
